    "• Soft Prompts Storage: For each dataset D k, we store a separate soft prompt P k with m prompt tokens, each ofTABLE I: Datasets statistics.",
    "Dataset D human D vicuna D llama D chatgpt Total # true news 2,500 500 501 501 4002 # disinformation 2,500 326 557 587 3970 dimension d. The total space required for all soft prompts across m datasets is:O(m • m • d) = O(m 2 • d)(9)• Intermediate Representations: During inference, the hidden states H are stored.",
    "The space complexity for these representations is:O((n + m • m) • d) = O((n + m 2) • d)(10)Combining these components, the overall space complexity is:O(|θ| + m 2 • d + (n + m 2) • d)(11)This can be simplified to:O(|θ| + m 2 • d + n • d)(12)In summary, the computational complexity of our proposed method DELD is primarily dominated by the inference complexity of the pre-trained model and the storage requirements for the soft prompts and intermediate representations.The time complexity is O(n 2 • d • L + m 2 • d), and the space complexity is O(|θ| + m 2 • d + n • d).These complexities highlight the efficiency of DELD in adapting to evolving disinformation while maintaining computational feasibility.",
